                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.5151/158: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-11T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 11, 1939—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 11—11:43 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>142. With reference to the exchange situation, arrears for imports from the
                    United States in 1938 have been completely liquidated and 1939 applications for
                    exchange transfer permits filed up to February 20 have been paid. Transfers will
                    probably be slow but regular until tobacco purchases start in early December
                    when large transfers are expected.</p>
                <p>Inform Commerce.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
